sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Webhook as ODH Notebook Webhook<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS mTLS
    participant Controller as ODH Notebook Controller<br/>Reconciler
    participant ImageAPI as ImageStream API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant OAuth as OpenShift OAuth<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Proxy as OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Notebook as Notebook Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP

    rect rgb(220, 240, 255)
        Note over User,ImageAPI: Flow 1: Notebook Creation (OAuth Enabled)
        User->>K8sAPI: Create Notebook CR<br/>kubectl apply<br/>Auth: User Credentials
        K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate-notebook-v1<br/>mTLS<br/>Auth: K8s API Client Cert
        Webhook->>ImageAPI: Resolve ImageStream<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
        ImageAPI-->>Webhook: Docker Image Digest
        Webhook->>Webhook: Inject OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>Add Reconciliation Lock<br/>Mount CA Bundle
        Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated Notebook Spec
        K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch Event: Notebook Created
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ServiceAccount<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Service ({notebook-name}-tls)<br/>Port: 443:8443/TCP
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Secret (oauth-config)<br/>Random Cookie Secret
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Secret (tls cert)<br/>via service.beta annotation
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Route<br/>Reencrypt TLS Mode
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicies<br/>ctrl-np + oauth-np
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Verify ServiceAccount ImagePullSecrets
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Remove Reconciliation Lock
        Note over Controller: Notebook pod now starts
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over User,Notebook: Flow 2: Notebook Access (OAuth Enabled)
        User->>Router: HTTPS GET https://{route-host}/<br/>Auth: None (initial)
        Router->>Proxy: Forward to OAuth Proxy<br/>Reencrypt TLS
        Proxy->>Proxy: Check OAuth Cookie
        Proxy->>OAuth: Redirect to OAuth Login<br/>OAuth 2.0 Flow
        OAuth-->>User: Login Page
        User->>OAuth: Authenticate<br/>OpenShift Credentials
        OAuth-->>Proxy: OAuth Callback + Token
        Proxy->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview (SAR)<br/>Resource: notebooks.kubeflow.org/{name}<br/>Verb: get<br/>Auth: User Token
        K8sAPI-->>Proxy: Allowed/Denied
        alt Authorized
            Proxy->>Proxy: Set OAuth Cookie
            Proxy->>Notebook: Forward Request<br/>HTTP/8888 (localhost)
            Notebook-->>Proxy: Jupyter UI Response
            Proxy-->>Router: HTTPS Response
            Router-->>User: Jupyter Notebook Interface
        else Denied
            Proxy-->>Router: 403 Forbidden
            Router-->>User: Access Denied
        end
    end

    rect rgb(255, 240, 240)
        Note over User,Notebook: Flow 3: Notebook Access (Non-OAuth)
        User->>Router: HTTPS GET https://{route-host}/<br/>Auth: None
        Router->>Notebook: Forward to Notebook<br/>HTTP/8888<br/>Edge TLS (terminated)
        Notebook-->>Router: Jupyter UI Response
        Router-->>User: Jupyter Notebook Interface
    end

    rect rgb(255, 255, 220)
        Note over K8sAPI,ImageAPI: Flow 4: Webhook Admission
        K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate-notebook-v1<br/>Notebook Create/Update<br/>mTLS Auth
        Webhook->>ImageAPI: GET ImageStream (optional)<br/>Namespaces: opendatahub, redhat-ods-applications<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
        ImageAPI-->>Webhook: Image Digest Reference
        Webhook->>Webhook: Inject OAuth Proxy (if annotated)<br/>Mount CA ConfigMaps<br/>Set ENV vars
        Webhook-->>K8sAPI: AdmissionReview Response<br/>Patched Notebook Spec
    end
